SPORTS stakeholders and well-wishers here have been asked to rescue Kisiwani FC from Pemba Island to enable the team return home after the end of their league match today. The assistance is also needed to enable the team to finish their Premier League games. The team faces financial constraints, a situation that has ruined the team’s performance, according to its head coach Masoud Seif. The Daily News reporter who visited the team’s camp at Kibele, Unguja South Zanzibar, found the players and officials in a pathetic situation. The coach said they were in Unguja Island since March 1st this year and their performance has not been impressive due to the financial woes. “We are facing a volatile situation; things have turned from bad to worse. We urgently need financial assistance,” said the coach. On 6m/- the team received from Zanzibar Football Federation (ZFF) being sponsors’ backing, the official coach said the funding was not sufficient and now they are penniless. According to the coach, the team spends about 40,000/- daily while 50,000/- is spent on transport from their camp to Amaan stadium. “We are hungry close to starvation,” he said. “I am doing everything here, all other officials have deserted the camp, the team since March 19th this year,” he sadly said. Adding the team’s players Ali Mohammed Seif and Shabani Koma said they are facing a tough survival and they don’t know how their problem will be solved. They asked the well-wishers to rescue them by providing them food and transport to Pemba after today's league game. Glued at the bottom of Isles top flight league, Kisiwani will face Zimamoto today in their last league game. The Isles league will be suspended in the coming Holly Month of Ramadhan.